section.section:
The BayStat Subcabinet is composed of:
The Secretary of Natural Resources;
The Secretary of the Environment;
The Secretary of Planning;
The Secretary of Agriculture;
The President of the University of Maryland Center for Environmental Science;
The Dean of the College of Agriculture and Natural Resources at the University of Maryland, College Park; and
The chair of the Critical Area Commission for the Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays.

text.section:
The BayStat Program shall:
Provide accurate and timely data to policymakers and the public about the efficacy and cost-effectiveness of local, State, and federal programs to restore the Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays;
Track and assess the progress of State and federal programs to improve the health of the Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays;
Assess the effectiveness of enforcement programs in curbing pollution and achieving Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays restoration goals and institute actions to improve the effectiveness of enforcement programs;
Adopt measurable goals for Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays restoration;
Identify new threats to the health of the Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays;
Increase public awareness of, and participation in, efforts to restore the vitality of the Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays; and
Direct the administration of the Trust Fund.
